Sequence
It is one of the most simplest type of workflow used to arrange activities in a linear order.


2. Flowchart
It is one of the workflow design type used to represent automation processes in a visual diagram-like structure.




---

PC-2

1. Decision-making
It means choosing which path the workflow should follow based on condition.


2. Looping
Looping lets you repeat a set of activities until a condition is met.




---

PC-3

1. Recorder
It is a tool used to capture user action of an application and convert them into automation sequence.



Basic Recorder – Generates a linear sequence of activities.

Desktop – Used for automating desktop applications.

Web – Designed for web browser-based automation.

Citrix – Designed for virtual environment (such as Citrix, Remote recorder).



---

PC-4
Excel Automation
It is an automation process of using UiPath activities to read, write, receive, send and automate data.


---

PC-5
PDF Automation
It is the process of using UiPath activities to extract complete data from PDF files.


---

PC-6

1. Keyboard activities – They are used to type text, enter, tab etc.


2. Mouse activities – They are used to perform actions such as clicking, hovering, or dragging.




---

PC-7

1. Screen scraping – It is used to extract data from the selected screen or window.


2. Data scraping – It is used to extract structured data from web application or websites.




---

PC-8

1. PDF automation – It is used to read data from PDF files.


2. Exception handling – It ensures that automation does not break when error occurs.




---

PC-9
Email automation
It is an automation process of using UiPath to read, receive, send and automate daily.
